headline: Union Pacific (UNP): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Since September 2024, Union Pacific has been in a holding pattern, posting a small loss of 1.9% while floating around $247.85. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 3.8% gain during that period.
